title: Grading the Buckeyes: Turnovers mar offense’s performance
text:
Posted: 10:26 p.m. Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015 Grading the Buckeyes: Turnovers mar offense’s performance View Larger David Jablonski/Staff Ohio State's Ezekiel Elliott breaks free for a touchdown in the third quarter against Indiana on Saturday, Oct. 3, 2015, at Memorial Stadium in Bloomington, Ind. David Jablonski/Staff Staff Writer COLUMBUS — 
Ohio State fans from Columbus to Dayton to Athens to Cleveland to Toledo and beyond will wring their hands for the next week, wondering how a team expected to be one of the best in school history could almost lose to Indiana. 
The Buckeyes likely will remain No. 1 this week after beating Indiana 34-27 on Saturday at Memorial Stadium, but they don’t look like a national championship team.
